itemDescription: Church of England clergyman and antiquary

wikipedia_page.main: John Wood Warter (1806–1878) was an English cleric and antiquarian. He is known now as an editor of the works of Robert Southey, his friend.

response: John Wood Warter (1806-1878), antiquarian and cleric and editor of the works of Robert Southey, was born at Cruckmeole.
** Southey's Common-place Book: First Series, and Second Series (each series in a separate volume), edited by John Wood Warter, poetry and prose
